---
name: generate-unit-test
type: command
description: Generate or update high-quality deterministic unit tests
---

Generate comprehensive unit tests for the currently selected function.

## Coverage Requirements

Tests must include:

- Happy path
- Edge cases
- Invalid input
- Null/undefined handling
- Boundary conditions
- Unexpected data types if applicable

## Assertion Quality Requirements

- Do NOT use assert.ok()
- Do NOT use non-strict assertions
- Avoid vague boolean checks
- Assert exact return values
- For objects and arrays, compare full expected structure
- Tests must fail for incorrect implementations

## Determinism Requirement

Tests must be deterministic and explicit.
Avoid assumptions.
Define full expected outputs.

## Self-Review Phase

After generating tests:

1. Review all assertions.
2. If any assertion is weak, vague, or non-deterministic:
   - Rewrite it to be stronger.
3. Ensure compliance with all project testing rules.

Return ONLY the final improved test cases.
Do not include explanations.
